+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GpiE2JDWeV2sHSu9PyA7n4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# T14: Financial Ledger\n     2→\n     3→**Category:** bugfix/hard\n     4→**Timeout:** 30 minutes\n     5→\n     6→## Description\n     7→\n     8→You're maintaining a double-entry accounting ledger library. The library tracks accounts, journal entries (transactions), and provides reporting functions (trial balance, account statements, P&L).\n     9→\n    10→Several bugs have been reported. The test suite has 40 tests, but only 31 are currently passing (8 bugs cause 9 test failures). Your job is to fix all the bugs so that all 40 tests pass.\n    11→\n    12→## Architecture\n    13→\n    14→The library is in `src/ledger.ts` and exports:\n    15→\n    16→- `Ledger` class with methods:\n    17→  - `createAccount(name, type, currency?)` — Create a named account (asset, liability, equity, revenue, expense). Optional currency defaults to \"USD\".\n    18→  - `postEntry(description, debits, credits, date?)` — Post a journal entry with debit/credit line items. Each line is `{ account: string, amount: number }`. Debits must equal credits. Optional date defaults to now.\n    19→  - `getBalance(accountName)` — Get current balance for an account. Assets/expenses have normal debit balances; liabilities/equity/revenue have normal credit balances.\n    20→  - `getTrialBalance()` — Returns all account balances. Total debits must equal total credits.\n    21→  - `getStatement(accountName, startDate?, endDate?)` — Returns chronological list of entries affecting an account, with running balance.\n    22→  - `splitEntry(description, fromAccount, toAccounts, totalAmount, date?)` — Convenience method: split a total amount across multiple destination accounts. `toAccounts` is `{ account: string, amount: number }[]`. Creates a journal entry debiting `fromAccount` and crediting each destination.\n    23→  - `getAccountsByType(type)` — Returns all accounts of a given type.\n    24→  - `getProfitAndLoss(startDate?, endDate?)` — Returns revenue minus expenses for the period.\n    25→\n    26→## Known Issues\n    27→\n    28→Users have reported:\n    29→1. Trial balance doesn't balance in some scenarios\n    30→2. Account statements show wrong running balances\n    31→3. Split entries sometimes create unbalanced journal entries\n    32→4. Date filtering in statements is off-by-one\n    33→5. P&L calculation has sign errors\n    34→6. Currency mismatch validation isn't working\n    35→7. Duplicate account names aren't rejected\n    36→8. getBalance returns wrong sign for liability accounts\n    37→\n    38→## Validation\n    39→\n    40→```bash\n    41→npm test      # Run tests (32/40 passing currently)\n    42→npm run build # Should compile cleanly\n    43→npm run lint  # Should pass\n    44→```\n    45→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XhYN1cPpQS9V4Ng5VN8XMH","session_id":"2e0d2146-8dc8-4a82-8626-c137ae57e1db","uuid":"89e9bf4f-fb54-43e5-bdda-7227e93ec20b"}
